 Lady Frere - Crime Combating Cluster Task Team conducted  operation around Glengrey area on Tuesday. "During operation  members followed up information proceeded to a certain house where they arrested a 50-year-old woman in dealing in dagga   and also closed unlicensed liquor outlets," said police spokesperson, Captain Namhla Mdleleni. "Suspect will appear before Lady Frere Magistrate's Court soon." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 